     2| * IVX Enterprise Realtime — Redis adapter for multi-instance Socket.IO
     3| *
     4| * When REDIS_URL is present, Socket.IO uses the Redis adapter so that
     5| * messages broadcast across all backend instances. This enables:
     6| *   - Multi-instance chat synchronization
     7| *   - Cross-instance presence tracking
     8| *   - Duplicate message prevention via dedup keys
     9| *   - Automatic reconnect with session recovery
    10| *
    11| * When REDIS_URL is absent, falls back to in-memory adapter (single instance).
    12| */
    13|import type { Server as SocketIOServer } from 'socket.io';
    14|
    15|const ADAPTER_MARKER = 'ivx-realtime-redis-adapter-2026-07-14';
    16|
    17|export type RealtimeAdapterConfig = {
    18|  enabled: boolean;
    19|  redisUrl: string | null;
